
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the value of the [fruit] node is "orange" using the [eq] slot. If the condition is true, it sets the value of the [category] node to "Citrus" using the [set-value] slot. The [if] slot evaluates the condition and executes the [.lambda] block if the condition is met.
if
   eq:x:@.fruit
      .:orange
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.category
         .:Citrus
